    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are CSS Units?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "CSS units define the size of elements, text, spacing, and layout. They are categorized into absolute and relative units."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Absolute Units"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Absolute units have fixed values and do not change based on screen size."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "css",
      "value": "p {\n  font-size: 16px;\n  width: 200px;\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Absolute Units"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Unit", "Description"],
        "rows": [
          ["px", "Pixels (most common)"],
          ["cm", "Centimeters"],
          ["mm", "Millimeters"],
          ["in", "Inches"],
          ["pt", "Points"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Relative Units"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Relative units adjust based on parent elements or screen size, making them ideal for responsive design."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "css",
      "value": "p {\n  font-size: 1.5em;\n}\n\n.container {\n  width: 50%;\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Relative Units"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Unit", "Description"],
        "rows": [
          ["%", "Relative to parent element"],
          ["em", "Relative to parent font size"],
          ["rem", "Relative to root font size"],
          ["vw", "Viewport width (1vw = 1% of screen width)"],
          ["vh", "Viewport height (1vh = 1% of screen height)"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Example Comparison"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "css",
      "value": "h1 {\n  font-size: 2rem;\n}\n\n.box {\n  width: 50vw;\n  height: 30vh;\n}"
    },
